{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":640,"text":"We can cut violent deaths\naround the world"},{"time":5870,"text":"by 50 percent in the next three decades."},{"time":10120,"text":"All we have to do\nis drop killing by 2.3 percent a year,"},{"time":15191,"text":"and we'll hit that target."}]},{"cues":[{"time":17644,"text":"You don't believe me?"},{"time":19339,"text":"Well, the leading epidemiologists\nand criminologists around the world"},{"time":22613,"text":"seem to think we can, and so do I,"},{"time":25004,"text":"but only if we focus on our cities,\nespecially the most fragile ones."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30139,"text":"You see, I've been thinking\nabout this a lot."},{"time":34408,"text":"For the last 20 years, I've been working"},{"time":36320,"text":"in countries and cities\nripped apart by conflict,"},{"time":39888,"text":"violence, terrorism, or some\ninsidious combination of all."},{"time":43905,"text":"I've tracked gun smugglers\nfrom Russia to Somalia,"},{"time":47411,"text":"I've worked with warlords\nin Afghanistan and the Congo,"},{"time":50583,"text":"I've counted cadavers in Colombia, in \nHaiti, in Sri Lanka, in Papua New Guinea."},{"time":56285,"text":"You don't need to be\non the front line, though,"},{"time":58535,"text":"to get a sense that our planet\nis spinning out of control, right?"},{"time":61847,"text":"There's this feeling that international\ninstability is the new normal."},{"time":66396,"text":"But I want you to take a closer look,"},{"time":68527,"text":"and I think you'll see that\nthe geography of violence is changing,"},{"time":71739,"text":"because it's not so much our nation states\nthat are gripped by conflict and crime"},{"time":75547,"text":"as our cities: Aleppo, Bamako, Caracas, \nErbil, Mosul, Tripoli, Salvador."},{"time":83071,"text":"Violence is migrating to the metropole."}]},{"cues":[{"time":86196,"text":"And maybe this is to be expected, right?"},{"time":88921,"text":"After all, most people today,\nthey live in cities, not the countryside."},{"time":92868,"text":"Just 600 cities, including 30 megacities,\naccount for two thirds of global GDP."},{"time":98704,"text":"But when it comes to cities,"},{"time":100463,"text":"the conversation is\ndominated by the North,"},{"time":103122,"text":"that is, North America, Western Europe,\nAustralia and Japan,"},{"time":106521,"text":"where violence is \nactually at historic lows."},{"time":109668,"text":"As a result, city enthusiasts, they talk\nabout the triumph of the city,"},{"time":114369,"text":"of the creative classes, and the mayors\nthat will rule the world."},{"time":118315,"text":"Now, I hope that mayors\ndo one day rule the world,"},{"time":121801,"text":"but, you know, the fact is,"},{"time":123838,"text":"we don't hear any conversation, really,\nabout what is happening in the South."},{"time":128207,"text":"And by South, I mean\nLatin America, Africa, Asia,"},{"time":132584,"text":"where violence in some\ncases is accelerating,"},{"time":135312,"text":"where infrastructure is overstretched,"},{"time":137913,"text":"and where governance is sometimes\nan aspiration and not a reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":142268,"text":"Now, some diplomats\nand development experts and specialists,"},{"time":146591,"text":"they talk about 40 to 50 fragile states"},{"time":149256,"text":"that will shape security\nin the 21st century."},{"time":152878,"text":"I think it's fragile cities which will\ndefine the future of order and disorder."},{"time":158063,"text":"That's because warfare\nand humanitarian action"},{"time":161414,"text":"are going to be\nconcentrated in our cities,"},{"time":163628,"text":"and the fight for development,"},{"time":165201,"text":"whether you define that\nas eradicating poverty,"},{"time":167892,"text":"universal healthcare,\nbeating back climate change,"},{"time":170325,"text":"will be won or lost in the shantytowns,\nslums and favelas of our cities."},{"time":175996,"text":"I want to talk to you about four megarisks"},{"time":178552,"text":"that I think will define\nfragility in our time,"},{"time":181801,"text":"and if we can get to grips with these,"},{"time":184030,"text":"I think we can do something\nwith that lethal violence problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":186975,"text":"So let me start with some good news."},{"time":189347,"text":"Fact is, we're living in the most\npeaceful moment in human history."},{"time":194778,"text":"Steven Pinker and others have shown how\nthe intensity and frequency of conflict"},{"time":198959,"text":"is actually at an all-time low."},{"time":201699,"text":"Now, Gaza, Syria, Sudan, Ukraine,"},{"time":205345,"text":"as ghastly as these conflicts are,\nand they are horrific,"},{"time":209176,"text":"they represent a relatively\nsmall blip upwards"},{"time":211916,"text":"in a 50-year-long secular decline."},{"time":214911,"text":"What's more, we're seeing\na dramatic reduction in homicide."},{"time":219218,"text":"Manuel Eisner and others have shown"},{"time":221435,"text":"that for centuries, we've seen\nthis incredible drop in murder,"},{"time":225145,"text":"especially in the West."},{"time":227090,"text":"Most Northern cities today are 100 times\nsafer than they were just 100 years ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":232526,"text":"These two facts -- the decline in armed \nconflict and the decline in murder --"},{"time":236271,"text":"are amongst the most extraordinary,"},{"time":237950,"text":"if unheralded, accomplishments\nof human history,"},{"time":240527,"text":"and we should be really excited, right?"},{"time":243827,"text":"Well, yeah, we should."},{"time":245655,"text":"There's just one problem:\nThese two scourges are still with us."},{"time":250044,"text":"You see, 525,000 people --\nmen, women, boys and girls --"},{"time":256148,"text":"die violently every single year."},{"time":259329,"text":"Research I've been doing\nwith Keith Krause and others"},{"time":261929,"text":"has shown that between 50,000 and 60,000\npeople are dying in war zones violently."},{"time":267386,"text":"The rest, almost 500,000 people,\nare dying outside of conflict zones."},{"time":272400,"text":"In other words, 10 times more people\nare dying outside of war than inside war."},{"time":278393,"text":"What's more, violence is moving south,\n"},{"time":281488,"text":"to Latin America and the Caribbean,"},{"time":284196,"text":"to parts of Central and Southern Africa,"},{"time":286477,"text":"and to bits of the Middle East\nand Central Asia."},{"time":289351,"text":"Forty of the 50 most dangerous \ncities in the world"},{"time":292120,"text":"are right here in Latin America,"},{"time":293658,"text":"13 in Brazil,"},{"time":295528,"text":"and the most dangerous of all, it's \nSan Pedro Sula, Honduras' second city,"},{"time":300765,"text":"with a staggering homicide rate\nof 187 murders per 100,000 people."},{"time":305581,"text":"That's 23 times the global average."}]},{"cues":[{"time":308720,"text":"Now, if violence is\nre-concentrating geographically,"},{"time":311447,"text":"it's also being reconfigured\nto the world's new topography,"},{"time":314260,"text":"because when it comes to cities,\nthe world ain't flat,"},{"time":316799,"text":"like Thomas Friedman likes to say."},{"time":319077,"text":"It's spiky."},{"time":320413,"text":"The dominance of the city\nas the primary mode of urban living"},{"time":324327,"text":"is one of the most extraordinary\ndemographic reversals in history,"},{"time":328614,"text":"and it all happened so fast."},{"time":331702,"text":"You all know the figures, right?"},{"time":333227,"text":"There's 7.3 billion people\nin the world today;"},{"time":335469,"text":"there will be 9.6 billion by 2050."},{"time":337858,"text":"But consider this one fact:"},{"time":339922,"text":"In the 1800s, one in 30\npeople lived in cities,"},{"time":343114,"text":"today it's one in two,"},{"time":345634,"text":"and tomorrow virtually everyone\nis going to be there."},{"time":348792,"text":"And this expansion in urbanization\nis going to be neither even nor equitable."},{"time":352878,"text":"The vast majority, 90 percent,"},{"time":354521,"text":"will be happening in the South,\nin cities of the South."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358737,"text":"So urban geographers and demographers,"},{"time":361864,"text":"they tell us that it's not necessarily\nthe size or even the density of cities"},{"time":366159,"text":"that predicts violence, no."},{"time":368249,"text":"Tokyo, with 35 million people,"},{"time":370501,"text":"is one of the largest, and some might say\nsafest, urban metropolises in the world."},{"time":375229,"text":"No, it's the speed of\nurbanization that matters."},{"time":378976,"text":"I call this turbo-urbanization, and it's \none of the key drivers of fragility."}]},{"cues":[{"time":384823,"text":"When you think about the incredible\nexpansion of these cities,"},{"time":389611,"text":"and you think about turbo-urbanization,\nthink about Karachi."},{"time":393218,"text":"Karachi was about 500,000 people in 1947,\na hustling, bustling city."},{"time":399127,"text":"Today, it's 21 million people,"},{"time":402824,"text":"and apart from accounting\nfor three quarters of Pakistan's GDP,"},{"time":406769,"text":"it's also one of the most violent\ncities in South Asia."},{"time":409863,"text":"Dhaka, Lagos, Kinshasa,"},{"time":412667,"text":"these cities are now 40 times larger\nthan they were in the 1950s."}]},{"cues":[{"time":417542,"text":"Now take a look at New York."},{"time":419440,"text":"The Big Apple, it took 150 years\nto get to eight million people."},{"time":424636,"text":"SÃ£o Paulo, Mexico City, took 15\nto reach that same interval."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429947,"text":"Now, what do these medium,\nlarge, mega-, and hypercities look like?"},{"time":433840,"text":"What is their profile?"},{"time":435379,"text":"Well, for one thing, they're young."},{"time":437214,"text":"What we're seeing in many of them\nis the rise of the youth bulge."},{"time":440836,"text":"Now, this is actually a good news story."},{"time":442748,"text":"It's a function of reductions\nin child mortality rates."},{"time":445338,"text":"But the youth bulge is something\nwe've got to watch."},{"time":447795,"text":"What it basically means"},{"time":449226,"text":"is the proportion of young people\nliving in our fragile cities"},{"time":452125,"text":"is much larger than those living \nin our healthier and wealthier ones."},{"time":455627,"text":"In some fragile cities,"},{"time":457146,"text":"75 percent of the population\nis under the age of 30."},{"time":460727,"text":"Think about that:\nThree in four people are under 30."},{"time":465479,"text":"It's like Palo Alto on steroids."},{"time":468324,"text":"Now, if you look at Mogadishu for example,"},{"time":471064,"text":"in Mogadishu the mean age is 16 years old."},{"time":475174,"text":"Ditto for Dhaka, Dili and Kabul."},{"time":478076,"text":"And Tokyo? It's 46."},{"time":480828,"text":"Same for most Western European cities."},{"time":484229,"text":"Now, it's not just youth\nthat necessarily predicts violence."},{"time":487409,"text":"That's one factor among many,"},{"time":489453,"text":"but youthfulness combined\nwith unemployment, lack of education,"},{"time":492429,"text":"and -- this is the kicker -- \nbeing male, is a deadly proposition."},{"time":496535,"text":"They're statistically correlated,\nall those risk factors, with youth,"},{"time":500036,"text":"and they tend to relate\nto increases in violence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":504033,"text":"Now, for those of you who are\nparents of teenage sons,"},{"time":507358,"text":"you know what I'm talking about, right?"},{"time":509304,"text":"Just imagine your boy\nwithout any structure"},{"time":512214,"text":"with those unruly friends of his,\nout there cavorting about."},{"time":515915,"text":"Now, take away the parents,"},{"time":518106,"text":"take away the education,\nlimit the education possibilities,"},{"time":522476,"text":"sprinkle in a little bit of drugs,\nalcohol and guns,"},{"time":525721,"text":"and sit back and watch the fireworks."},{"time":528924,"text":"The implications are disconcerting."},{"time":531021,"text":"Right here in Brazil,\nthe life expectancy is 73.6 years."},{"time":534536,"text":"If you live in Rio, I'm sorry,\nshave off two right there."},{"time":538211,"text":"But if you're young, you're uneducated,"},{"time":540498,"text":"you lack employment,\nyou're black, and you're male,"},{"time":543012,"text":"your life expectancy drops\nto less than 60 years old."},{"time":546224,"text":"There's a reason why youthfulness\nand violence are the number one killers"},{"time":551081,"text":"in this country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":553422,"text":"Okay, so it's not all doom\nand gloom in our cities."},{"time":556696,"text":"After all, cities are hubs of innovation,"},{"time":559064,"text":"dynamism, prosperity, \nexcitement, connectivity."},{"time":562653,"text":"They're where the smart people gather."},{"time":564905,"text":"And those young people I just mentioned,"},{"time":566846,"text":"they're more digitally savvy\nand tech-aware than ever before."},{"time":570490,"text":"And this explosion, the Internet,\nand mobile technology,"},{"time":574064,"text":"means that the digital divide\nseparating the North and the South"},{"time":577779,"text":"between countries\nand within them, is shrinking."},{"time":581029,"text":"But as we've heard so many times,"},{"time":582644,"text":"these new technologies\nare dual-edged, right?"},{"time":585376,"text":"Take the case of law enforcement."},{"time":587519,"text":"Police around the world are starting\nto use remote sensing and big data"},{"time":591106,"text":"to anticipate crime."},{"time":592701,"text":"Some cops are able to predict\ncriminal violence before it even happens."},{"time":597121,"text":"The future crime scenario,\nit's here today,"},{"time":600526,"text":"and we've got to be careful."},{"time":602026,"text":"We have to manage the issues\nof the public safety"},{"time":604321,"text":"against rights to individual privacy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":606987,"text":"But it's not just the cops\nwho are innovating."},{"time":609138,"text":"We've heard extraordinary activities\nof civil society groups"},{"time":611982,"text":"who are engaging in local \nand global collective action,"},{"time":615117,"text":"and this is leading to digital protest\nand real revolution."},{"time":619740,"text":"But most worrying\nof all are criminal gangs"},{"time":623136,"text":"who are going online\nand starting to colonize cyberspace."},{"time":626045,"text":"In Ciudad JuÃ¡rez in Mexico,\nwhere I've been working,"},{"time":629177,"text":"groups like the Zetas\nand the Sinaloa cartel"},{"time":631531,"text":"are hijacking social media."},{"time":633152,"text":"They're using it to recruit,\nto sell their products,"},{"time":635736,"text":"to coerce, to intimidate and to kill."},{"time":637966,"text":"Violence is going virtual."}]},{"cues":[{"time":641149,"text":"So this is just a partial sketch"},{"time":643282,"text":"of a fast-moving and dynamic\nand complex situation."},{"time":645958,"text":"I mean, there are many other megarisks"},{"time":647807,"text":"that are going to define\nfragility in our time,"},{"time":650242,"text":"not least income inequality,"},{"time":652141,"text":"poverty, climate change, impunity."},{"time":655879,"text":"But we're facing a stark dilemma"},{"time":658224,"text":"where some cities are going to thrive\nand drive global growth"},{"time":662283,"text":"and others are going to stumble\nand pull it backwards."},{"time":665219,"text":"If we're going to change course,\nwe need to start a conversation."},{"time":668445,"text":"We can't only focus\non those cities that work,"},{"time":671436,"text":"the Singapores, the Kuala Lumpurs,"},{"time":673944,"text":"the Dubais, the Shanghais."},{"time":675824,"text":"We've got to bring those fragile cities\ninto the conversation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":680028,"text":"One way to do this might be\nto start twinning"},{"time":682558,"text":"our fragile cities with our healthier\nand wealthier ones,"},{"time":685298,"text":"kickstarting a process of learning\nand collaboration"},{"time":687811,"text":"and sharing of practices,\nof what works and what doesn't."},{"time":692050,"text":"A wonderful example of this is coming\nfrom El Salvador and Los Angeles,"},{"time":695642,"text":"where the mayors in San Salvador\nand Los Angeles are collaborating"},{"time":699802,"text":"on getting ex-gang members\nto work with current gang members,"},{"time":703755,"text":"offering tutoring, education,"},{"time":706543,"text":"and in the process are helping\nincubate cease-fires and truces,"},{"time":709863,"text":"and we've seen homicide rates\ngo down in San Salvador,"},{"time":712410,"text":"once the world's most violent city,"},{"time":714233,"text":"by 50 percent."},{"time":715877,"text":"We can also focus \non hot cities, but also hot spots."},{"time":718426,"text":"Place and location matter fundamentally\nin shaping violence in our cities."},{"time":722728,"text":"Did you know that between\none and two percent"},{"time":725283,"text":"of street addresses in any fragile city"},{"time":727348,"text":"can predict up to 99 percent\nof violent crime?"},{"time":731050,"text":"Take the case of SÃ£o Paulo,\nwhere I've been working."},{"time":733614,"text":"It's gone from being Brazil's most\ndangerous city to one of its safest,"},{"time":737367,"text":"and it did this by doubling down"},{"time":739326,"text":"on information collection,\nhot spot mapping, and police reform,"},{"time":742557,"text":"and in the process, it dropped homicide\nby 70 percent in just over 10 years."},{"time":747595,"text":"We also got to focus on those hot people."},{"time":750050,"text":"It's tragic, but being young,\nunemployed, uneducated, male,"},{"time":754139,"text":"increases the risks\nof being killed and killing."},{"time":758136,"text":"We have to break this cycle of violence"},{"time":760821,"text":"and get in there early with our children,\nour youngest children,"},{"time":764155,"text":"and valorize them, not stigmatize them."},{"time":767214,"text":"There's wonderful work that's happening\nthat I've been involved with"},{"time":770584,"text":"in Kingston, Jamaica\nand right here in Rio,"},{"time":772875,"text":"which is putting education,\nemployment, recreation"},{"time":776173,"text":"up front for these high-risk groups,"},{"time":778329,"text":"and as a result, we're seeing violence\ngoing down in their communities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":781684,"text":"We've also got to make our cities safer,\nmore inclusive, and livable for all."},{"time":785362,"text":"The fact is, social cohesion matters."},{"time":789129,"text":"Mobility matters in our cities."},{"time":791609,"text":"We've got to get away from this model\nof segregation, exclusion,"},{"time":794679,"text":"and cities with walls."},{"time":796095,"text":"My favorite example of how to do this\ncomes from MedellÃ­n."},{"time":798905,"text":"When I lived in Colombia\nin the late 1990s,"},{"time":800910,"text":"MedellÃ­n was the murder capital \nof the world, but it changed course,"},{"time":804541,"text":"and it did this by deliberately investing\nin its low-income and most violent areas"},{"time":808800,"text":"and integrating them\nwith the middle-class ones"},{"time":811208,"text":"through a network of cable cars,"},{"time":812880,"text":"of public transport,\nand first-class infrastructure,"},{"time":815527,"text":"and in the process, it dropped homicide\nby 79 percent in just under two decades."}]},{"cues":[{"time":820349,"text":"And finally, there's technology."},{"time":823119,"text":"Technology has enormous\npromise but also peril."},{"time":825901,"text":"We've seen examples here\nof extraordinary innovation,"},{"time":828449,"text":"and much of it coming from this room,"},{"time":830242,"text":"The police are engaging \nin predictive analytics."},{"time":832610,"text":"Citizens are engaging\nin new crowdsourcing solutions."},{"time":835200,"text":"Even my own group is involved\nin developing applications"},{"time":837847,"text":"to provide more accountability over police\nand increase safety among citizens."},{"time":842199,"text":"But we need to be careful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":845687,"text":"If I have one single\nmessage for you, it's this:"},{"time":849076,"text":"There is nothing inevitable\nabout lethal violence,"},{"time":852561,"text":"and we can make our cities safer."},{"time":857312,"text":"Folks, we have the opportunity\nof a lifetime to drop homicidal violence"},{"time":863358,"text":"in half within our lifetime."},{"time":866005,"text":"So I have just one question:"},{"time":867738,"text":"What are we waiting for?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":869283,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":871067,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}